ch and data to inform the platform strategy provide analysis and recommendation for new features optimizations and other methods to improve the overall enduser experience engage with crossfunctional teams on the evaluation of new payment products and loyalty programs act a subjectmatter expert in advising stakeholders on how to enable productsprograms on the mobile platform   required qualifications   bachelors degree in information technology software engineering or other technology fields a minimum of  years of experience in product management of mobile or other digital platform applications strong understanding of platform service models including platform as a service paas experience in project management agile development methodologies and ability to manage multiple teams across vendors strong analytical skills for making product decisions and rapid product iteration strategic thinking and demonstrated proactive problem solving experience in leading discussions with business and technology stakeholders developing use cases and value propositions   preferred qualifications   master’s degree in information technology or business administration project management certifications motivated with desire to continue growth of knowledge in mobile commerce industry experience in retail industry   relocation options relocation will not be considered international considerations expatriate assignments will not be considered   chevron regrets that it is unable to sponsor employment visas or consider individuals on timelimited visa status for this position     regulatory disclosure for us positions   chevron is an equal opportunity  affirmative action employer  qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race color religion sex sexual orientation gender identity national origin disability or protected veteran status or other status protected by law or regulation   chevron participates in everify in certain locations as required by law   a