chevron station branded under the standard name in las vegas in  the federal government broke standard oil into several pieces under the sherman antitrust act one of those pieces standard oil co california went on to become chevron it became part of the seven sisters which dominated the world oil industry in the early th century in  the company changed its name to standard oil co of california socal by the terms of the breakup of standard oil at first standard of california could use the standard name only within its original geographic area of the pacific coast states plus nevada and arizona outside that area it had to use another name today chevron is the owner of the standard oil trademark in  states in the western and southeastern us to maintain ownership of the mark the company owns and operates one standardbranded chevron station in each state of the area although its status in kentucky is up in the air after chevron withdrew retail sales from kentucky in july  the chevron name came into use for some of its retail products in the s the name calso was also used from  to  in states outside its native west coast territory standard oil company of california ranked th among united states corporations in the value of world war ii military production contracts in  saudi arabia granted california standard a concession to find oil which led to the discovery of oil in  in  california standard discovered the worlds largest oil field in saudi arabia ghawar field california standards subsidiary californiaarabian standard oil company grew over the years and became the arabian american oil company aramco in  in  the saudi government began buying into aramco by  the company was entirely owned by the saudis and in  its name was changed to saudi arabian oil company—saudi aramcocitation needed standard oil of california and gulf oil merged in  which was the largest merger in history at that time to comply with us antitrust law california standard divested many of gulfs operating subsidiaries and sold some gulf stations and a refinery in the eastern united states the refinery is currently owned by sunoco among the assets sold off were gulfs retail outlets in gulfs home market of pittsburgh where chevron lacks a retail presence but does retain a regional headquarters there as of  partially for marcellus shalerelated drilling the same year standard oil of california also took the opportunity to change its legal name to chevron corporation since it had already been using the wellknown chevron retail brand name for decades chevron would sell the gulf oil trademarks for the entire us to cumberland farms the parent company of gulf oil lp in  after cumberland farms had a license to the gulf trademark in the northeastern united states since  in  chevron transferred its natural gas gathering operating and marketing operation to ngc corporation later dynegy in exchange for a roughly  equity stake in ngc in a merger completed february   illinova corp became a wholly owned subsidiary of dynegy inc and chevrons stake increased up to  however in may  chevron sold its stake in the company for approximately  million resulting in a gain of  million merger with texaco and postmergeredit on october   chevron announced acquisition of texaco in a deal valued at  billion creating the secondlargest oil company in the united states and the worlds fourthlargest publicly traded oil company with a combined market value of approximately  billion the merged company was named chevrontexaco on may   chevrontexaco announced it would drop the texaco moniker and return to the chevron name texaco remained as a brand under the chevron corporation on october   texaco purchased general motors share in gm ovonics which in  was restructured into cobasys a  joint venture between chevron and energy conversion devices ovonics in  both chevron and energy conservation devices sold their stakes in cobasys to sb limotive cocitation needed chevron gas station design used until  in  chevr